TI  - Japan vs. Silicon Valley: Quality-Cost Trade-Off Philosophies
JO  - Journal of International Business Studies
SP  - 289
EP  - 300
VL  - 21
IS  - 2
AB  - While Japanese manufacturing philosophies are said to be based on “quality is free” notions, it is commonly accepted that U.S. manufacturing centers on a “quality is costly” belief. This paper provides empirical data that test this conceptual division, seeking evidence about the quality tradeoff philosophies of U.S. and Japanese electronics manufacturing managers.
